RM  12206460
RT  Deoxyribonucleotide synthesis in anaerobic microorganisms: the class
RT  III ribonucleotide reductase.
RA  Fontecave M, Mulliez E, Logan DT;
RL  Prog Nucleic Acid Res Mol Biol. 2002;72:95-127.
CC  Ribonucleotide reductases (RNRs) are responsible for the conversion of
CC  the ribose sugar of RNA into the deoxyribose sugar of DNA. This is the
CC  rate-limiting step of DNA biosynthesis. The class III RNRs consist of
CC  two components, the catalytic enzyme (NrdD) and a radical-SAM domain
CC  enzyme (NrdG) which activates the catalytic enzyme by the generation of
CC  a protein-centered radical. 
